# MenuAR — AI Coding Rules
# These rules apply to all AI coding assistants in this project

## Project Context
This is MenuAR — a WebAR restaurant menu experience platform.
- Customer-facing: WebAR experience (scan QR → see 3D dishes in AR on table)
- Restaurant-facing: Dashboard to manage menu + 3D models
- Backend: Express API + PostgreSQL
- Always read CLAUDE.md first for full context

## Code Quality Rules

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always (`"strict": true` in tsconfig)
- No `any` types — use `unknown` with type guards if needed
- Define types/interfaces before implementing functions
- Shared types live in `packages/types/src/index.ts`

### React Components
- Functional components only — no class components
- Custom hooks for all complex logic (AR, data fetching, animations)
- Props must be typed with explicit interface (not inline)
- Keep components under 150 lines — extract if larger

### File naming
- Components: PascalCase.tsx (e.g., DishInfoPanel.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (e.g., useARScene.ts)
- Utils: camelCase.ts (e.g., modelLoader.ts)
- API routes: kebab-case (e.g., /api/v1/dish-views)

### AR / Three.js rules
- ALL Three.js logic lives in custom hooks or utility files, never in JSX
- Always dispose geometries, materials, textures on unmount
- Never load multiple models simultaneously — queue them
- Always handle the case where AR is not supported (iOS 15 and below, old Android)
- Cap renderer pixelRatio at 2: `Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 2)`

### API rules
- All routes use Zod validation on request body
- All errors return `{ error: string, code: string }` format
- Auth middleware on all `/dashboard` routes
- Rate limiting on all public routes

### Database
- Use Prisma transactions for multi-table operations
- Never use raw SQL unless absolutely necessary
- All queries go through service layer, never directly in routes

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT suggest native app approaches — we are WebAR only
- Do NOT add new npm packages without checking bundle size impact
- Do NOT put environment variables directly in code — always use process.env
- Do NOT store user personal data in the AR experience (anonymous only)
- Do NOT load all dish models at once — lazy load on tap
- Do NOT skip error handling in Three.js/Mind AR code — it fails silently

## Folder Boundaries
- `apps/web/src/ar/` — ONLY AR/Three.js code here
- `apps/web/src/components/` — ONLY React UI components, no AR logic
- `packages/api/src/services/` — business logic, external API calls
- `packages/api/src/routes/` — ONLY request/response handling, no business logic
- `packages/types/` — shared types only, no runtime code
